AIM:
Write a simple application, build a Docker image, and share the image to Docker Hub.

--------------------------------------------------
Step 1: Create Application
--------------------------------------------------

index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Docker Demo</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from Docker!</h1>
</body>
</html>

--------------------------------------------------
Step 2: Create Dockerfile
--------------------------------------------------

Dockerfile

FROM nginx:latest

COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

EXPOSE 80

--------------------------------------------------
Step 3: Build Docker Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker build -t docker-demo .

--------------------------------------------------
Step 4: Run Docker Container
--------------------------------------------------

docker run -d -p 8080:80 docker-demo

--------------------------------------------------
Step 5: Verify Application
--------------------------------------------------

Open Browser:

http://localhost:8080

Output:

Hello from Docker!

--------------------------------------------------
Step 6: Login to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker login

--------------------------------------------------
Step 7: Tag Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker tag docker-demo YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/docker-demo:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Step 8: Push Image to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker push YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/docker-demo:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Verify Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker images

docker pull YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/docker-demo:v1

--------------------------------------------------
RESULT
--------------------------------------------------

Successfully created a simple HTML application, built a Docker image, ran the container locally, and pushed the image to Docker Hub.
